    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 16,
        "summary": "Moab is condemned, and her people will sorrow\u2014The Messiah will sit on David's throne, seeking justice and hastening righteousness.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Send ye the lamb to the ruler of the land from Sela to the wilderness, unto the mount of the daughter of Zion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Send an appeal to the king of Judah, who then ruled also Edom.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 882
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it shall be, that, as a wandering bird cast out of the nest, so the daughters of Moab shall be at the fords of Arnon.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 21:13 (13\u201328).",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Take counsel, execute judgment; make thy shadow as the night in the midst of the noonday; hide the outcasts; bewray not him that wandereth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Give counsel. This begins Moab's appeal to Judah (vv.\u00a03\u20135).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let mine outcasts dwell with thee, Moab; be thou a covert to them from the face of the spoiler: for the extortioner is at an end, the spoiler ceaseth, the oppressors are consumed out of the land.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Let mine outcasts dwell with thee; be thou a covert for Moab.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:16.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in mercy shall the throne be established: and he shall sit upon it in truth in the tabernacle of David, judging, and seeking judgment, and hasting righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:47 (46\u201347).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Millennial Reign.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haste.",
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 150
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 2:11 (11\u201314).",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We have heard of the pride of Moab; he is very proud: even of his haughtiness, and his pride, and his wrath: but his lies shall not be so.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Beginning of Judah's reply, declining Moab's appeal.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pride.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 127
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall Moab howl for Moab, every one shall howl: for the foundations of Kir-hareseth shall ye mourn; surely they are stricken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:20 (20, 31).",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 3:25.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the fields of Heshbon languish, and the vine of Sibmah: the lords of the heathen have broken down the principal plants thereof, they are come even unto Jazer, they wandered through the wilderness: her branches are stretched out, they are gone over the sea.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 21:32.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 150
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 184
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore I will bewail with the weeping of Jazer the vine of Sibmah: I will water thee with my tears, O Heshbon, and Elealeh: for the shouting for thy summer fruits and for thy harvest is fallen.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And gladness is taken away, and joy out of the plentiful field; and in the vineyards there shall be no singing, neither shall there be shouting: the treaders shall tread out no wine in their presses; I have made their vintage shouting to cease.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:33.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 185,
                        "end": 190
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 212,
                        "end": 225
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore my bowels shall sound like an harp for Moab, and mine inward parts for Kir-haresh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 15:5; Jer. 48:36.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass, when it is seen that Moab is weary on the high place, that he shall come to his sanctuary to pray; but he shall not prevail.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This is the word that the Lord hath spoken concerning Moab since that time.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 2:1 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now the Lord hath spoken, saying, Within three years, as the years of an hireling, and the glory of Moab shall be contemned, with all that great multitude; and the remnant shall be very small and feeble.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 184
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 199
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}